ATTORNEY GRIEVANCE COMMISSION OF MARYLAND, Petitioner,
v.
Ann O. JARRELL, Respondent. Misc. Docket AG No. 70, Sept. Term, 2017 Court of Appeals of Maryland. March 27, 2018

ORDER

The Court of Appeals of Maryland, having considered the Joint Petition of the Attorney Grievance Commission and Respondent, Ann O. Jerrell, to place Respondent on Inactive Status by Consent pursuant to Maryland Rule 19-736(c), it is this 27th day of March, 2018;

ORDERED, that the Joint Petition be, and it is hereby GRANTED, and the Respondent, Ann O. Jarrell, is hereby placed on Inactive Status by consent; and it is further,

ORDERED, that the Clerk of this Court shall remove the name of Ann O. Jarrell from the register of attorneys in the Court and certify that fact to the Client Protection Fund of the Bar of Maryland and all Clerks of all judicial tribunals in this State in accordance with Maryland Rule 19-761.
